\": 0.9994504923782632, \"rank\": 0.000549791922031458, \"text\": \"Morocco\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morocco_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morocco_national_football_team\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"anything\", \"from\": 392, \"to\": 400}, {\"ngram\": \"even the opening ceremonies\", \"from\": 429, \"to\": 456}, {\"ngram\": \"this level\", \"from\": 471, \"to\": 481}, {\"ngram\": \"Andy Benesh\", \"from\": 496, \"to\": 507}, {\"ngram\": \"Miles Partain\", \"from\": 512, \"to\": 525}, {\"ngram\": \"21-12, 28-26 win\", \"from\": 546, \"to\": 562}, {\"ngram\": \"Zouheir Elgraoui\", \"from\": 605, \"to\": 621}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Nothing about the first 35 minutes of the match suggested anything out of the ordinary.\", \"from\": 624, \"to\": 711, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Nothing\", \"from\": 624, \"to\": 631}, {\"ngram\": \"the first 35 minutes\", \"from\": 638, \"to\": 658}, {\"ngram\": \"the match\", \"from\": 662, \"to\": 671}, {\"ngram\": \"anything\", \"from\": 682, \"to\": 690}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Benesh and Partain appeared urgent, focused, adjusting from an21-18, 21-18 opening-match lossto Cuba's Jorge Alayo and Noslen Diaz to regain the form that has them as the second seed in Pool D and the ninth overall.\", \"from\": 712, \"to\": 927, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 808, \"end\": 812, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cuba\", \"score\": 0.6491107560868548, \"rank\": 0.5400808967977342, \"text\": \"Cuba\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cuba\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cuba\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Benesh\", \"from\": 712, \"to\": 718}, {\"ngram\": \"Partain\", \"from\": 723, \"to\": 730}, {\"ngram\": \"an21\", \"from\": 772, \"to\": 776}, {\"ngram\": \"Noslen Diaz\", \"from\": 831, \"to\": 842}, {\"ngram\": \"the form\", \"from\": 853, \"to\": 861}, {\"ngram\": \"the second seed\", \"from\": 879, \"to\": 894}, {\"ngram\": \"Pool D\", \"from\": 898, \"to\": 904}, {\"ngram\": \"the ninth overall\", \"from\": 909, \"to\": 926}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Benesh and Partain, error-prone and blocked seven times by Alayo on Saturday, did not hit a single error during their 21-12 opening-set victory over Morocco.\", \"from\": 929, \"to\": 1086, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1078, \"end\": 1085, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morocco_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9994504923782632, \"rank\": 0.000549791922031458, \"text\": \"Morocco\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morocco_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morocco_national_football_team\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Alayo\", \"from\": 988, \"to\": 993}, {\"ngram\": \"Saturday\", \"from\": 997, \"to\": 1005}, {\"ngram\": \"a single error\", \"from\": 1019, \"to\": 1033}, {\"ngram\": \"their 21-12 opening-set victory\", \"from\": 1041, \"to\": 1072}]}, {\"sentence\": \"By the technical timeout of the second set, there were still zero American errors on the board, while Partain had kills on 12 of his 16 attempts.\", \"from\": 1087, \"to\": 1232, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1153, \"end\": 1161, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9952919886350952, \"rank\": 0.004730263694742841, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the technical timeout\", \"from\": 1090, \"to\": 1111}, {\"ngram\": \"the second set\", \"from\": 1115, \"to\": 1129}, {\"ngram\": \"the board\", \"from\": 1172, \"to\": 1181}, {\"ngram\": \"Partain\", \"from\": 1189, \"to\": 1196}, {\"ngram\": \"kills\", \"from\": 1201, \"to\": 1206}, {\"ngram\": \"his 16 attempts\", \"from\": 1216, \"to\": 1231}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It all added up to an 18-11 lead that seemed insurmountable.\", \"from\": 1233, \"to\": 1293, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an 18-11 lead\", \"from\": 1252, \"to\": 1265}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And then, bizarrely, the version of Benesh and Partain that was so convincing during that opening set and established a seven-point second set lead disappeared, replaced by the error-prone edition from Saturday.\", \"from\": 1295, \"to\": 1506, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"And then, bizarrely, the version\", \"from\": 1295, \"to\": 1327}, {\"ngram\": \"Benesh\", \"from\": 1331, \"to\": 1337}, {\"ngram\": \"Partain\", \"from\": 1342, \"to\": 1349}, {\"ngram\": \"that opening set\", \"from\": 1380, \"to\": 1396}, {\"ngram\": \"a seven-point second set lead\", \"from\": 1413, \"to\": 1442}, {\"ngram\": \"the error-prone edition\", \"from\": 1468, \"to\": 1491}, {\"ngram\": \"Saturday\", \"from\": 1497, \"to\": 1505}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Errors, mistakes of both the physical and mental variety compounded into a 9-2 Morocco run, sending the set well into overtime until, at long last, Benesh put it to an end with a block to seal the win, 25-23.\", \"from\": 1507, \"to\": 1715, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Errors\", \"from\": 1507, \"to\": 1513}, {\"ngram\": \"mistakes\", \"from\": 1515, \"to\": 1523}, {\"ngram\": \"both the physical and mental variety\", \"from\": 1527, \"to\": 1563}, {\"ngram\": \"a 9-2 Morocco run\", \"from\": 1580, \"to\": 1597}, {\"ngram\": \"the set\", \"from\": 1607, \"to\": 1614}, {\"ngram\": \"overtime\", \"from\": 1625, \"to\": 1633}, {\"ngram\": \"Benesh\", \"from\": 1655, \"to\": 1661}, {\"ngram\": \"an end\", \"from\": 1672, \"to\": 1678}, {\"ngram\": \"a block\", \"from\": 1684, \"to\": 1691}, {\"ngram\": \"the win\", \"from\": 1700, \"to\": 1707}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Until he did not.\", \"from\": 1717, \"to\": 1734, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Abicha, the 44-year-old defender competing in his second Olympic Games, challenged the block.\", \"from\": 1736, \"to\": 1829, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Abicha\", \"from\": 1736, \"to\": 1742}, {\"ngram\": \"the 44-year-old defender\", \"from\": 1744, \"to\": 1768}, {\"ngram\": \"his second Olympic Games\", \"from\": 1782, \"to\": 1806}, {\"ngram\": \"the block\", \"from\": 1819, \"to\": 1828}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Kevin Wong, doing analysis for NBC, laughed it off.\", \"from\": 1830, \"to\": 1881, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1830, \"end\": 1840, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kevin_Wong\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kevin Wong\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kevin_Wong\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kevin_Wong\"}, {\"begin\": 1861, \"end\": 1864, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\", \"score\": 0.9999995033468946, \"rank\": 4.952464074805009e-07, \"text\": \"NBC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"analysis\", \"from\": 1848, \"to\": 1856}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I call this the challenge from the grave,\\\" he said with a chuckle.\", \"from\": 1883, \"to\": 1950, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the challenge\", \"from\": 1896, \"to\": 1909}, {\"ngram\": \"the grave\", \"from\": 1915, \"to\": 1924}, {\"ngram\": \"a chuckle\", \"from\": 1940, \"to\": 1949}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It seemed a challenge out of frustration.\", \"from\": 1952, \"to\": 1993, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a challenge\", \"from\": 1962, \"to\": 1973}, {\"ngram\": \"frustration\", \"from\": 1981, \"to\": 1992}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Abicha was incensed before the point, arguing that Benesh was lathering up the ball in sweat prior to his serve.\", \"from\": 1994, \"to\": 2106, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Abicha\", \"from\": 1994, \"to\": 2000}, {\"ngram\": \"the point\", \"from\": 2021, \"to\": 2030}, {\"ngram\": \"Benesh\", \"from\": 2045, \"to\": 2051}, {\"ngram\": \"the ball\", \"from\": 2069, \"to\": 2077}, {\"ngram\": \"sweat\", \"from\": 2081, \"to\": 2086}, {\"ngram\": \"his serve\", \"from\": 2096, \"to\": 2105}]}, {\"sentence\": \"So he challenged for a net fault on Benesh, for seemingly no other reason than because he had one and he can not roll it over into their next match.\", \"from\": 2107, \"to\": 2255, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a net fault\", \"from\": 2128, \"to\": 2139}, {\"ngram\": \"Benesh\", \"from\": 2143, \"to\": 2149}, {\"ngram\": \"seemingly no other reason\", \"from\": 2155, \"to\": 2180}, {\"ngram\": \"their next match\", \"from\": 2238, \"to\": 2254}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But then, unbelievably, the challenge was successful.\", \"from\": 2257, \"to\": 2310, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the challenge\", \"from\": 2281, \"to\": 2294}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Even Wong and Chris Marlowe, doing play-by-play, could not believe it.\", \"from\": 2312, \"to\": 2382, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2326, \"end\": 2339, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chris_Marlowe\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Chris Marlowe\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q15117302\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chris_Marlowe\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chris_Marlowe\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Even Wong\", \"from\": 2312, \"to\": 2321}, {\"ngram\": \"play\", \"from\": 2347, \"to\": 2351}, {\"ngram\": \"play\", \"from\": 2355, \"to\": 2359}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The video showed the net moving, yes, but, as Benesh would emphatically argue after, it was the ball that clipped the net on the way down, not his arm.\", \"from\": 2383, \"to\": 2534, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The video\", \"from\": 2383, \"to\": 2392}, {\"ngram\": \"the net moving\", \"from\": 2400, \"to\": 2414}, {\"ngram\": \"Benesh\", \"from\": 2429, \"to\": 2435}, {\"ngram\": \"the ball\", \"from\": 2475, \"to\": 2483}, {\"ngram\": \"the net\", \"from\": 2497, \"to\": 2504}, {\"ngram\": \"the way\", \"from\": 2508, \"to\": 2515}, {\"ngram\": \"not his arm\", \"from\": 2522, \"to\": 2533}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Benesh attempted to challenge the challenge which, of course, did not happen.\", \"from\": 2535, \"to\": 2612, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Benesh\", \"from\": 2535, \"to\": 2541}, {\"ngram\": \"the challenge\", \"from\": 2565, \"to\": 2578}, {\"ngram\": \"course\", \"from\": 2589, \"to\": 2595}]}, {\"sentence\": \"On and on he argued - but on the match went, the crowd now fervently on the side of Morocco, the biggest underdogs on the men's side of these Olympic Games.\", \"from\": 2613, \"to\": 2769, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2697, \"end\": 2704, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morocco_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9994504923782632, \"rank\": 0.000549791922031458, \"text\": \"Morocco\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morocco_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morocco_national_football_team\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the match\", \"from\": 2642, \"to\": 2651}, {\"ngram\": \"the side\", \"from\": 2685, \"to\": 2693}, {\"ngram\": \"the biggest underdogs\", \"from\": 2706, \"to\": 2727}, {\"ngram\": \"the men's side\", \"from\": 2731, \"to\": 2745}, {\"ngram\": \"these Olympic Games\", \"from\": 2749, \"to\": 2768}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It could only do so much.\", \"from\": 2771, \"to\": 2796, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Benesh and Partain terminated every first-ball in side-out, and At 27-26, a Morocco overset was put away by Benesh to finish off what might not be the most memorable match of these Ol